var title_f35_18_36134="Acute liver failure - high power";
var content_f35_18_36134=[" <div id=\"graphicsToolbar\">",
"  <div id=\"graphicsCopy\">",
"   &copy;2013 UpToDate",
"   <sup>",
"    &reg;",
"   </sup>",
"  </div>",
"  <div id=\"graphicsLinks\">",
"   <a href=\"?imageKey=GAST%2F59723&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=1\" onclick=\"\">",
"    <img alt=\"Print this page\" src=\"./../images/icn_print.myextg\" title=\"Print this page\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink\" href=\"?imageKey=GAST%2F59723&amp;source=image_view&amp;view=print&amp;elapsedTimeMs=1\" onclick=\"\" title=\"Print this page\">",
"    Print",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"etacLink\" href=\"#\">",
"    <img alt=\"Email graphic(s)\" src=\"./../images/icn_email.myextg\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\"/>",
"   </a>",
"   <a class=\"icontxt textLink etacLink\" href=\"#\" title=\"Email graphic(s)\">",
"    Email",
"   </a>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
" <div class=\"graphic\">",
"  <div class=\"figure\" style=\"width: 470px\">",
"   <div class=\"ttl\">",
"    Acute liver failure (high power, Masson trichrome stain)",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"cntnt\" style=\"width: 450px; height: 353px; background-image: url(data:image/jpeg;base64,);\">",
"   </div>",
"   <div class=\"lgnd\">",
"    The only cells visible are macrophages, many filled with yellow-brown pigment granules. Lipofuscin (often called \"wear and tear pigment\") is composed of lipid-containing residues of lysosomal digestion. Its presence in high concentration in macrophages suggests extensive liver cell necrosis. The blue structures are all that remains of sinusoidal membranes that normally surround the hepatic plates.",
"    <div class=\"footnotes\">",
"    </div>",
"    <div class=\"reference\">",
"     Courtesy of Marshall M. Kaplan, MD.",
"    </div>",
"   </div>",
"  </div>",
" </div>",
"</div>"].join("\n");
